Telefônica Brasil: unit buys Terra Networks in intercompany deal

Tuesday, Jul 04, 2017



A subsidiary of Telefonica Brasil SA has bought a digital services provider from controlling shareholder SP Telecomunicacoes Participacoes SA, for 250 million reais ($76 million), in a bid to broaden the supply of corporate digital services.
In a Monday securities filing, Telefonica Brasil said subsidiary TData bought Terra Networks Brasil SA from SP Telecomunicacoes in cash; the price for Terra Networks was based on an appraisal made by KPMG
Telefonica Brasil, the owner of Brazil's largest mobile phone carrier Vivo, is seeking faster expansion of digital services as it moves away from a model based on offering voice and Internet connection
Preferred shares, Telefonica Brasil's most widely class of stock, are up 6 pct this year, compared with a 4.4 pct gain in Brazil's benchmark Bovespa stock index
 
Source:telecom.economictimes.indiatimes.com







 






















